><img src=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grim3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: =)</span><hr size=1> &quot;Every high-end Enchanter I know wants to be able to do more damage with their nukes. They should up Dementing Visions to 925 or so. You really can't tell me all you enjoy doing is buffing, debuffing, mezzing, and charming... can you?&quot;<br><br>Seems to me someone who plays an enchanter and doesn't like doing that stuff is pretty silly.  That's like saying &quot;who'd want to play a Warrior if all they do is hit stuff and taunt!?!?&quot;  That's THE CLASS, there wasn't any secret about it.  Enchanters nuke too much already in my book, like Clerics. <p><IMG SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg" ></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/8/02 12:40:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=724.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: =)</span><hr size=1> Excluding Kunark and old world zones, one possible solution would be to have manaburn have ZERO delay between recasts.  Being fully OOM after using it once gives us the need to sit down and med up again anyway.  The only problem with this is the pathetic 32k HP mobs from Kunark(including Venril Sathir in this).  So, get rid of the delay between manaburns, and we would probably be well balanced.<br><br>Putting damage bonuses to our spells based on our intelligence, or having the mana cost be lower based on intelligence, and total mana pool might also help.<br><br>Really, we suffer the most because stats don't affect individual spell damage output.  A level 60 wizard with sunstrike does IDENTICAL damage per cast to any other wizard with sunstrike(since summoned focus items are pretty much identical to the effect on items).<br><br> <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>Level 60 Wizard<br>The First Seal<br>The Nameless Server<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uraederle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raederle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/21/02 10:11:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=724.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What enchanters want</span><hr size=1> Unfortunately at the end game it's not buffing debuffing charming and mezzing, its buffing buffing buffing and buffing.   The first enchanter gets tash, the shammys are already fighting over slow and cripple, and the rest of the enchanters spend thier time twiddling their thumbs and snarling at verant.  <br><br>In a single exp group or on a fast moving crowd control raid I have neither space nor mana nor inclination to mem any booms and only the speicifically needed debuffing dots.  But when dealing with non mezzable zones (Kael etc) or the &quot;what crowds?&quot; boss mob, it woudl be nice to be more than wasted space.  After an enchanter for KEI/shiss and a second as backup we could be better replaced by any other class at that level.  Its at that point that enchanters start cussing out verant for leaving them nothing to do with their mana.<br><br>So sure, I want a better boom.  Something that has better mana efficiency than 250 mana for 650 damage landing one in 5 casts and not landing at all since by cast attempt 4 the super high taunt has me aggroed and dead.   I dont need a scad of lines of booms, I *don't* want to be a better boomer than mages druids or wizzies, I just want some way to spend my mana on offense not defense.   My greatest fear is that Verant in caster balancing will look at the enchanters and say &quot;Balanced, no probs&quot; or worse yet &quot;not balanced, lets give the whores more buffs to make all the *other* players happy with&quot;..<br>Meredeth 60 ench, Tunare<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uharrije.showPublicProfile?language=EN>harrije</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/22/02 6:32:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=724.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Mage perspective</span><hr size=1> First, the recent pet changes have really increased the ability of magicians to contribute to raid damage. Pet &quot;problems&quot; are about 85-90% reduced with <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /pet hold</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and new pet coding measures, and the other 10-15% can usually be avoided by careful paying of attention. So basically, even on nasty multi-mob raids, I can send in a pet to attack and watch it out of the corner of my eye while I drop a few mod rods for the healers. And if I can't devote enough time to watching the pet, I can tell it to hold and have 100% guarantee that it will sit there until I tell it to do something else or it dies.<br><br>Still, I suggest the following be taken into consideration:<br><br>*) In Jewish mythology, a golem was an animated being constructed from the powers of earth, wind, fire, and water. Given that magicians are nominally masters of those four elements, it would seem appropriate that magicians could also have some line of spells for controlling these beings. If magicians deserve some kind of bane spell, and if the devs don't want it to be too horribly unbalanced, then some form of golem-bane would be appropriate. It would give magicians a new little niche to play with, and it would add some roleplay value (yeah, not a big issue I realize, but still).<br><br>*) Barring that, stretch the definition a bit and consider various golems and constructs as summoned beings and give the versus-summon spells a lower resist rate, including golems currently immune or nearly so to magic attacks (spite golems, black reavers, etc.)<br><br>*) Consider some form of pet-only weapon with a low-resist proc or high ATK and combat stats specifically for designated uber encounters. Make the summoned items zonebound (similar to PoA keys...rentable but not zoneable) and make the spells castable only in certain designated zones such as Kael or Skyshrine. The weapons could also be tagged only for a specific mob model (such as Giant) so as not to give magicians in, say, Velketors Labyrinth any advantage with the spiders and gargoyles when the weapon was only intended to contribute to the Velketor battle itself. This would help magicians better utilize pets on large raids without throwing typical game balance askew. The spells don't have to be common, they can be quested similar to wizard bane spells. Heck, they can even use a fairly costly reagent. The goal is just to give pets (all pets) an edge where they need it most: making physical contact with level 61+ mobs.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=724.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=724.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=724.topic&index=13><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif borde